# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# sdfmt is the **D code formatter** from snazzy-d/sdc
# (Snazzy D Compiler) — formats D source code per the
# D style guide.  Pivots from Zig std.process.argsAlloc
# (R288 cyber) into the **D language tooling cluster**.
# Sister to dmd / dub / dscanner (other D tools).
# **MAJOR MILESTONE**: corpus's **first documented D
# std.getopt CLI** — adds D to the cross-language CLI
# taxonomy (28 library variants now).
#
# Critical extraction note: sdfmt uses **D's stdlib
# `std.getopt`** library at `import std.getopt` —
# corpus's **first documented D CLI**.  `std.getopt`
# is **the** standard D CLI parsing library — built
# into the D stdlib (Phobos).  Used by dmd (D
# compiler), dub (D package manager), dscanner, and
# most D CLI tooling.  Extends the **cross-language
# CLI taxonomy** to TWENTY-EIGHT library variants:
# Rust (6), Go (4), Python (3), Crystal OptionParser
# (R269), Haskell optparse-applicative (R270), OCaml
# Cmdliner (R271), C POSIX getopt (R272), Java picocli
# (R276), Kotlin clikt (R277), Scala decline (R278),
# Dart args (R279), Ruby OptionParser (R280), Perl
# Getopt::Long (R281), PHP Symfony Console (R282),
# Swift ArgumentParser (R283), F# Argu (R284), Lua
# argparse (R285), C# System.CommandLine (R286), Nim
# parseopt (R287), Zig std.process.argsAlloc (R288),
# **D std.getopt** (R289 — NEW).  **MAJOR PATTERN
# MILESTONE**: 28 cross-language CLI library variants
# documented.
#
# Critical extraction note: sdfmt uses **VARIADIC
# getopt call with NAME / HELP / ADDRESS triplets**
# at sdfmt.d:9-15:
# ```d
#   auto help_info = getopt(
#       args, std.getopt.config.caseSensitive,
#       "debug", "Enable debug", &dbg,
#       "i", "Format files in place", &inPlace,
#   );
# ```
# Each option is specified as 3 consecutive args:
# (1) NAME with optional `|short` suffix (e.g.
# `"help|h"`), (2) HELP text, (3) ADDRESS-OF target
# variable.  Documents the **D variadic triplet
# argument pattern** — distinct from Perl's
# `'name|short=type' => \var` pairs (R281 cpanm),
# Ruby's `parser.on(name, help) { |v| ... }` block
# (R280 reek), and Lua's `parser:option(name, help)`
# chained calls (R285 luacheck).  D's variadic
# approach is the MOST COMPACT for many flags —
# everything in a single function call.  Corpus's
# **first documented variadic triplet CLI pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: sdfmt uses **`std.getopt
# .config.caseSensitive`** at sdfmt.d:11 — passes a
# CONFIG FLAG IN THE ARGS LIST.  D's std.getopt
# accepts config flags interleaved with option
# specifications.  Each `std.getopt.config.X` value
# applies to ALL options declared AFTER it (until
# another config flag overrides it).  Documents the
# **inline-config-flag pattern** — distinct from
# Perl Getopt::Long's `Getopt::Long::Configure("bundling")`
# called as a separate statement (R281 cpanm).  D's
# approach EMBEDS the config in the same call.
# Other D config flags include `passThrough`,
# `keepEndOfOptions`, `noBundling`, `noBundlingValue`.
# Corpus's **first documented inline-config CLI
# pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: sdfmt uses **`help_info
# .helpWanted` auto-detection** at sdfmt.d:17 — D's
# std.getopt automatically detects when `--help` or
# `-h` was passed by the user.  The returned struct
# has a `.helpWanted` bool that's true if either was
# given.  Documents the **auto-help-detection**
# pattern — distinct from R287 nimpretty's manual
# `of "help", "h":` case dispatch and from R273
# irust's hand-rolled `show_help` field.  D's
# approach is built into the library.  Corpus's
# **first documented auto-helpWanted detection**.
#
# Critical extraction note: sdfmt uses **`help_info
# .options`** for METADATA REFLECTION at sdfmt.d:
# 23-34 — `help_info.options` is an array of option
# metadata structs, each with `.optShort`, `.optLong`,
# `.help` fields.  Used for CUSTOM HELP FORMATTING:
# the developer iterates the array and writes
# customized help output.  Documents the **option-
# metadata reflection pattern** — D's std.getopt
# EXPOSES the parsed option definitions for runtime
# introspection.  Distinct from clap derive's no-
# direct-reflection (R247+) and from Symfony's
# inheritance-based help generation (R282 peridot).
# Useful for tools that need NON-STANDARD help
# formatting (sdfmt uses a custom format with
# `%-16s` for option alignment).  Corpus's **first
# documented runtime option-metadata reflection**.
#
# Critical extraction note: sdfmt uses **`catch
# (GetOptException ex)`** at sdfmt.d:38 — D's
# std.getopt throws an exception on parse errors
# (e.g., unknown flag).  The application catches it
# and handles gracefully.  Documents the **exception-
# based error handling** for CLI parsing in D —
# distinct from C's getopt return-code (R272 blink),
# Rust's Result types (R273+), and Go's manual
# checking (R263 lazygit).  D's approach is OO-style
# — errors are exceptions thrown by the library.
# Pattern documented in 2 languages now: PHP
# Symfony Console (R282 peridot) + D std.getopt
# (R289 sdfmt).
#
# Critical extraction note: sdfmt uses **`// sdfmt
# off` / `// sdfmt on`** SELF-REFERENTIAL DIRECTIVES
# at sdfmt.d:10 + 14 — sdfmt's own code-formatting
# directives are used INSIDE sdfmt's source to
# disable formatting around the getopt call (which
# uses unusual indentation for readability).
# Documents the **self-referential meta-formatting
# pattern** — corpus's first documentation of a CLI
# tool USING ITS OWN DIRECTIVES in its source.
# Distinct from `.editorconfig` (external config)
# and from clang-format pragmas (#define-style).
# Plus the directives are line comments `//` which
# get preserved through formatting.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line

# 2 flags decoded source-direct from sdfmt.d:11-14.
# Note: sdfmt's getopt uses ONLY long names with
# `i` for in-place mode (single character).
_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help (std.getopt auto-detected via helpWanted)]' \
  '--debug[enable debug output]' \
  '-i[format files in place]' \
  '*:D source file:_files -g "*.d"'
